last_episode_to_air.name: Back in Black
last_episode_to_air.overview: The New Orleans small-tire list gets its second shakeup of the season as Scott, the number one big-tire driver, rolls out a small-tire car. Shannon hopes to mount a comeback. Meanwhile, Brandon is determined to win against unbeaten number one, Bobby.

name: Street Outlaws: New Orleans
overview: This time instead of being in the 405 this show will take us to the Big Easy; New Orleans! Featuring no one else but Big Chief's number one enemy, Kye Kelly his third generation Camaro The Shocker. Big Chief claims that Kye Kelly is the one and only person he has not beat yet. Chief is so set on beating Kye Kelly that he now has a Promod called the Crowmod which his first goal is to use to beat Kye Kelly!

episodes.name: New Orleans: Heads I Win, Tails You Lose
episodes.overview: A Tennessee crew calls out the New Orleans racers. Also, Shane prepares his Mustang with the help of Travis and Scott.

episodes.name: Houston, We Have a Problem
episodes.overview: The New Orleans crew competes with the Houston team. Kye suffers mechanical issues that might have him out of the race completely; Brandon faces Sonoma; Scott and Jerry have a fight.

episodes.name: The Shocker Shakeup
episodes.overview: The New Orleans team returns for list racing; Shannon's '69 Chevelle targets Bobby's spot on the small-tire list; Shane's Nova tries to crack the big tire list; Barry refuses to race Jerry Bird.

episodes.name: AlaBAM!
episodes.overview: The New Orleans team meets up with the Alabama team after the big-tire racers refuse to end their feud.

episodes.name: Raiders of the Lost Ark-ansas
episodes.overview: Kye and Bobby call out Arkansas; the Birds fight to get their car straight; Kye plays a prank on Scott Taylor; an alternate road interferes with the home-field advantage.

episodes.name: When the Saints Come Driving In
episodes.overview: The season closes with hardcore list racing; Kye and Bobby have targets on their backs; Travis fights to stay and Jason tries to fend off Barry.

episodes.name: Building a Team in The Big Easy
episodes.overview: The NOLA Outlaws look back on a wild season building their team. Featuring previously unaired races, outtakes, and new interviews, this episode shows how close the team came to falling apart before even getting started.

episodes.name: Highway to Hell
episodes.overview: Kye Kelley invites three new drivers to try out for the top-five big-tire list. Kye tries to take the number one spot back from Scott Taylor. Bobby must also defend his top spot against number two, Brandon Smith.

episodes.name: A Long Way to the Top
episodes.overview: Bobby Ducote shakes up the small-tire list by inviting three new racers to try out; teammates Shane Lester, Travis Santa Cruz and Shannon Poole vow to send any new guys packing; Bobby must defend his top spot against No. 2, Brandon Smith.

episodes.name: Thunderstruck
episodes.overview: Kye wants to call out another top team. And the perfect opponent is Houston - featuring James "Birdman" Finney, David Bird Jones, and Barefoot Ronnie Pace. The NOLA team barely tied Houston last year, and both sides are craving a rematch.

episodes.name: Moneytalks
episodes.overview: After a win over Houston, the New Orleans team is ready for bigger competition. Kye and the big-tire list head to Texas for Dignight - a single elimination shootout with the fastest street cars in the country, with a prize of more than twelve grand.

episodes.name: Shook Me All Night Long
episodes.overview: After a disappointing showing at Dignight, Kye decides to shake up the big-tire list again. He brings in newcomer David Bird Jones, a Houston transplant, along with Shane Lester and gives them a shot at the top five.

episodes.name: Back in Black
episodes.overview: The New Orleans small-tire list gets its second shakeup of the season as Scott, the number one big-tire driver, rolls out a small-tire car. Shannon hopes to mount a comeback. Meanwhile, Brandon is determined to win against unbeaten number one, Bobby.

episodes.name: Hells Bells
episodes.overview: Kye accepts a callout from a smack-talking Georgia team. The NOLA crew travels Savannah, where they meet the crew that features the cocky Andy Mac, the old veteran Willy Dog, and team leader Jeff Miller, who drives a pro-mod Camaro called Bumblebee.

episodes.name: Walk All Over You
episodes.overview: Kye wants the number one big-tire spot back from Scott. But when Barry calls Kye out first, it brings tensions to a boil. Bobby organizes a small-tire shootout, bringing top racers from around the country to New Orleans for a single-elimination tournament

episodes.name: T.N.T.
episodes.overview: After a successful season, the NOLA racers decide to loosen things up with a crash-up derby, using junker cars towing trailers. They find rides at the salvage yard and swipe trailers from family for the big showdown.
